{
  "texts": [
    "This is unsurprising, given the high cost associated with human-based evaluation.",
    "In this category, Saha et al. (2023) evaluate the model's immutability, including how well humans can generalize to the model's reasoning patterns with new, unseen inputs based on the provided explanations.",
    "Comparison to ground truth: ground truth evaluation involves comparing the generated explanations with human-annotated textual explanations (Wiegreffe and Marasovic, 2021), considered ground truth for evaluating explanations.",
    "This lack of ground-truth evaluation relates to our earlier point in 4.1.2, highlighting the lack of explainable datasets for ATS, where we only encountered one paper.",
    "We use this section to reiterate the need to extend the work on constructing datasets with human-annotated explanations for ATS."
  ]
}